One Real BEM Violation (You Should Fix This)
❌ Problem
<p className={styles['principles__description--narrow']}>


In BEM, a modifier cannot exist alone.
It must modify a base class, not replace it.

✅ Correct Usage
<p className={`${styles.principles__description} ${styles['principles__description--narrow']}`}>

✅ Correct CSS Pattern
.principles__description {
  color: var(--color-gray-300);
  text-align: center;
  max-width: 320px;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.principles__description--narrow {
  max-width: 260px;
}


This is textbook BEM.